{"type":"system","subtype":"task_started","task_id":"aa0f989952167f37e","tool_use_id":"toolu_01DYUGkaDmeivE9DdDR2ug9Z","description":"Explore safety-relevant source code","task_type":"local_agent","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the Cloche codebase to find all safety-relevant implementation details. I need to understand:\n\n1. **Container network configuration**: How Docker containers are configured, network allowlisting, what network settings are available. Look in internal/adapters/ for Docker-related code, and in any container configuration.\n\n2. **Host-side prompt handling**: How prompts are prepared and passed to containers. Look in internal/host/, .cloche/prompts/, .cloche/scripts/, and anywhere prompt templates are referenced.\n\n3. **Container isolation**: How the container model works — file copying, overlay handling, what gets mounted vs copied. Look in internal/adapters/docker/ or similar.\n\n4. **Workflow DSL security**: Any security-relevant aspects of the workflow DSL — step permissions, result handling, abort conditions.\n\n5. **Network allowlisting**: grep for \"allowlist\", \"network\", \"whitelist\", \"firewall\" in source code.\n\n6. **Agent adapter security**: How agent adapters work, what access they have, how they're sandboxed.\n\n7. **Any existing security documentation** in docs/.\n\nSearch broadly across the entire codebase. Look at Dockerfiles in .cloche/, configuration files, and all Go source code.","uuid":"f3b32cf4-bfa5-4b11-88c6-15a0a432b0bb","session_id":"dbf10f22-a7e0-4657-b5f4-9a1bc4f6ad20"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Thoroughly explore the Cloche codebase to find all safety-relevant implementation details. I need to understand:\n\n1. **Container network configuration**: How Docker containers are configured, network allowlisting, what network settings are available. Look in internal/adapters/ for Docker-related code, and in any container configuration.\n\n2. **Host-side prompt handling**: How prompts are prepared and passed to containers. Look in internal/host/, .cloche/prompts/, .cloche/scripts/, and anywhere prompt templates are referenced.\n\n3. **Container isolation**: How the container model works — file copying, overlay handling, what gets mounted vs copied. Look in internal/adapters/docker/ or similar.\n\n4. **Workflow DSL security**: Any security-relevant aspects of the workflow DSL — step permissions, result handling, abort conditions.\n\n5. **Network allowlisting**: grep for \"allowlist\", \"network\", \"whitelist\", \"firewall\" in source code.\n\n6. **Agent adapter security**: How agent adapters work, what access they have, how they're sandboxed.\n\n7. **Any existing security documentation** in docs/.\n\nSearch broadly across the entire codebase. Look at Dockerfiles in .cloche/, configuration files, and all Go source code."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01DYUGkaDmeivE9DdDR2ug9Z","session_id":"dbf10f22-a7e0-4657-b5f4-9a1bc4f6ad20","uuid":"05b10638-6136-42f8-ae56-f0fd1ba66394"}
